hpnicfLIActive.name: hpnicfLIActive
hpnicfLIActive.description: This Notification is sent when a type of intercepting configuration is changed from inactive to active. The value of the hpnicfLIStreamtype which identify the actual intercept stream is included in this notification.

hpnicfLITimeOut.name: hpnicfLITimeOut
hpnicfLITimeOut.description: When the time specified in hpnicfLIMediationTimeout arrives, the device notifies the manager corresponding intercept is removed.

hpnicfLIFailureInformation.name: hpnicfLIFailureInformation
hpnicfLIFailureInformation.description: When interception is configured on distributed device, the configuration perhaps failed on some board. If this happened, this notification will occur.

hpnicfLINewIndex.name: hpnicfLINewIndex
hpnicfLINewIndex.description: This object will be used as an index value for a new hpnicfLIMediationEntry. Whenever read, the agent will give a non-used value. This is to reduce the probability of conflict during creation of new hpnicfLIMediationTable entries.

hpnicfLIMediationTable.name: hpnicfLIMediationTable
hpnicfLIMediationTable.description: This table describes interception gateway information with which interception device communicates.

hpnicfLIMediationEntry.name: hpnicfLIMediationEntry
hpnicfLIMediationEntry.description: An entry of configuring mediation device.

hpnicfLIMediationIndex.name: hpnicfLIMediationIndex
hpnicfLIMediationIndex.description: hpnicfLIMediationIndex is a entry identifier. The Mediation Device should be responsible for making sure these are unique. Before creating a new entry, a value for this variable may be obtained by reading hpnicfLINewIndex to reduce the probability of a value collision.

hpnicfLIMediationDestAddr.name: hpnicfLIMediationDestAddr
hpnicfLIMediationDestAddr.description: The IP Address of the Mediation Device to receive intercepted traffic.

hpnicfLIMediationDestPort.name: hpnicfLIMediationDestPort
hpnicfLIMediationDestPort.description: The L4-port number on the Mediation Device to receive intercepted traffic.

hpnicfLIMediationSrcInterface.name: hpnicfLIMediationSrcInterface
hpnicfLIMediationSrcInterface.description: The interface on the intercepting device from which to transmit intercepted data. If zero, intercepting device will select an outbound interface according to hpnicfLIMediationDestAddr.

hpnicfLIMediationDscp.name: hpnicfLIMediationDscp
hpnicfLIMediationDscp.description: The Differentiated Services Code Point the intercepting device applies to the IP packets encapsulating the intercepted traffic.

hpnicfLIMediationTimeOut.name: hpnicfLIMediationTimeOut
hpnicfLIMediationTimeOut.description: The time at which this row and all related Stream Table rows should be automatically removed, and the intercept function expire.

hpnicfLIMediationTransport.name: hpnicfLIMediationTransport
hpnicfLIMediationTransport.description: The protocol used in transferring intercepted data to the Mediation Device.

hpnicfLIMediationNotificationEnable.name: hpnicfLIMediationNotificationEnable
hpnicfLIMediationNotificationEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of any notifications or informs by the MIB agent for this table entry.

hpnicfLIMediationRowStatus.name: hpnicfLIMediationRowStatus
hpnicfLIMediationRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfLIStreamTable.name: hpnicfLIStreamTable
hpnicfLIStreamTable.description: This table lists the traffic stream's type to be intercepted. The specified filter is defined in hpnicfLIIPStreamTable, hpnicfLIMACStreamTable or hpnicfLIUserStreamTable, according to hpnicfLIStreamtype. Also it contains counters for packets to be intercepted and dropped by attached type of filter.

hpnicfLIStreamEntry.name: hpnicfLIStreamEntry
hpnicfLIStreamEntry.description: A single type of data stream to be intercepted.

hpnicfLIStreamIndex.name: hpnicfLIStreamIndex
hpnicfLIStreamIndex.description: The index of the stream entry.

hpnicfLIStreamtype.name: hpnicfLIStreamtype
hpnicfLIStreamtype.description: Identifies the type of stream, and according to it uses filter table. It can not be changed after a filter table is attached to it. The following types of streams are supported: ip: IP filter. The exact definition is a row in hpnicfLIIPStreamTable. mac: MAC filter. The exact definition is a row in hpnicfLIMACStreamTable. userConnecton: User connection filter. The exact definition is a row in hpnicfLIUserStreamTable.

hpnicfLIStreamEnable.name: hpnicfLIStreamEnable
hpnicfLIStreamEnable.description: If 'true', the interception is active. And it is set to 'true' only after an additional filter specification has been attached to this stream.

hpnicfLIStreamPackets.name: hpnicfLIStreamPackets
hpnicfLIStreamPackets.description: The numbers of packets that have been intercepted.

hpnicfLIStreamDrops.name: hpnicfLIStreamDrops
hpnicfLIStreamDrops.description: The numbers of packets were dropped in the lawful intercept process.

hpnicfLIStreamHPackets.name: hpnicfLIStreamHPackets
hpnicfLIStreamHPackets.description: The numbers of packets have been intercepted. This object is a 64-bit version of hpnicfLIStreamPackets.

hpnicfLIStreamHDrops.name: hpnicfLIStreamHDrops
hpnicfLIStreamHDrops.description: The numbers of packets were dropped in the lawful intercept process. This object is a 64-bit version of hpnicfLIStreamDrops.

hpnicfLIStreamRowStatus.name: hpnicfLIStreamRowStatus
hpnicfLIStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfLIIPStreamTable.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamTable
hpnicfLIIPStreamTable.description: This table lists the IPv4 and IPv6 streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hpnicfLIMediationTable and hpnicfLIStreamTable.

hpnicfLIIPStreamEntry.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamEntry
hpnicfLIIPStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hpnicfLIStreamTable. The second index permits multiple classifiers to be used together, such as having an IP address as source or destination.

hpnicfLIIPStreamInterface.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamInterface
hpnicfLIIPStreamInterface.description: Traffic received or transmitted over this interface will be intercepted. This value must be set when creating a stream entry, either zero, or a valid interface index. If the value is zero, interception accepts any interface. Then at least one additional parameter must be selected, and not be default value.

hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType
hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.description: The type of address, used in packet selection.

hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddr.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddr
hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddr.description: The Destination address used in packet selection. This address will be consistent with the type specified in hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.

hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddrLength.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddrLength
hpnicfLIIPStreamDestAddrLength.description: The length of the Destination Prefix. A value of zero means all addresses to match. This prefix length will be consistent with the type specified in hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.

hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddr.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddr
hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddr.description: The Source Address used in packet selection. This address will be consistent with the type specified in hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.

hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength
hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcAddrLength.description: The length of the Source Prefix. A value of zero means all addresses to match. This prefix length will be consistent with the type specified in hpnicfLIIPStreamAddrType.

hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByte.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByte
hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByte.description: The value of the TOS byte. If hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByte&(~hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByteMask)!=0, configuration is rejected.

hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByteMask.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByteMask
hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByteMask.description: This value is ANDed with the value of the TOS byte in a packet and compared with hpnicfLIIPStreamTosByte. If the values are equal, the comparison is equal. If both the mask and the TosByte value are zero, the result is to always accept.

hpnicfLIIPStreamFlowId.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamFlowId
hpnicfLIIPStreamFlowId.description: The flow identifier in an IPv6 header. -1 indicates that the Flow Id is unused.

hpnicfLIIPStreamProtocol.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamProtocol
hpnicfLIIPStreamProtocol.description: The IP protocol to match against the IPv4 protocol number or the IPv6 Next- Header number in the packet.

hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin
hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin.description: The minimum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match. This value must be equal to or less than the value specified for this entry in hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax. If both hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin and hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin is equal to hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax
hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax.description: The maximum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry. This value must be equal to or greater than the value specified for this entry in hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin. If both hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin and hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMin is equal to hpnicfLIIPStreamDestL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin
hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin.description: The minimum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match. This value must be equal to or less than the value specified for this entry in hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax. If both hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin and hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin is equal to hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax
hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax.description: The maximum value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry. This value must be equal to or greater than the value specified for this entry in hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin. If both hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin and hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax are at their default values, the port number is effectively unused. If hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMin is equal to hpnicfLIIPStreamSrcL4PortMax, only one port number to be intercepted.

hpnicfLIIPStreamVRF.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamVRF
hpnicfLIIPStreamVRF.description: It is the name of a Virtual Routing and Forwarding (VRF) of a VPN.

hpnicfLIIPStreamRowStatus.name: hpnicfLIIPStreamRowStatus
hpnicfLIIPStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfLIMACStreamTable.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamTable
hpnicfLIMACStreamTable.description: This table lists the IEEE 802 streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hpnicfLIMediationTable and hpnicfLIStreamTable.

hpnicfLIMACStreamEntry.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamEntry
hpnicfLIMACStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hpnicfLIStreamTable. The second index permits multiple classifiers to be used together, such as having an MAC address as source or destination.

hpnicfLIMACStreamFields.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamFields
hpnicfLIMACStreamFields.description: This object displays what attributes will be compared to identify traffic. interface: indicates that traffic on the stated interface is to be intercepted dstMacAddress: indicates that traffic destined to a given address should be intercepted srcMacAddress: indicates that traffic sourced from a given address should be intercepted ethernetPid: indicates that traffic with a stated Ethernet Protocol Identifier should be intercepted dSap: indicates that traffic with an certain 802.2 LLC Destination SAP should be intercepted sSap: indicates that traffic with an certain 802.2 LLC Source SAP should be intercepted At least one of the bits has to be set in order to activate an entry. If multiple bits are set, traffic to be intercepted must be satisfied with all set attributes.

hpnicfLIMACStreamInterface.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamInterface
hpnicfLIMACStreamInterface.description: Traffic received or transmitted over this interface will be intercepted. This value must be set when creating a stream entry, either zero, or a valid interface index. If the value is zero, interception accepts any interface. Additional parameter must be selected together.

hpnicfLIMACStreamDestAddr.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamDestAddr
hpnicfLIMACStreamDestAddr.description: The Destination address used in packet selection.

hpnicfLIMACStreamSrcAddr.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamSrcAddr
hpnicfLIMACStreamSrcAddr.description: The Source Address used in packet selection.

hpnicfLIMACStreamEthPid.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamEthPid
hpnicfLIMACStreamEthPid.description: The value of the Ethernet Protocol Identifier in the Ethernet traffic or IEEE 802.2 SNAP traffic.

hpnicfLIMACStreamDSap.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamDSap
hpnicfLIMACStreamDSap.description: The value of the IEEE 802.2 Destination SAP.

hpnicfLIMACStreamSSap.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamSSap
hpnicfLIMACStreamSSap.description: The value of the IEEE 802.2 Source SAP.

hpnicfLIMACStreamRowStatus.name: hpnicfLIMACStreamRowStatus
hpnicfLIMACStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfLIUserStreamTable.name: hpnicfLIUserStreamTable
hpnicfLIUserStreamTable.description: This table lists the user connection streams to be intercepted. It is associated with hpnicfLIMediationTable and hpnicfLIStreamTable.

hpnicfLIUserStreamEntry.name: hpnicfLIUserStreamEntry
hpnicfLIUserStreamEntry.description: A single stream to be intercepted. The first index indicates the Mediation Device. The second index is that of the stream's counter entry in the hpnicfLIStreamTable. This permits multiple classifiers to be used together.

hpnicfLIUserStreamAcctSessID.name: hpnicfLIUserStreamAcctSessID
hpnicfLIUserStreamAcctSessID.description: This is the RADIUS attribute 44 acct-session-ID. The string must be set, and the length not be zero.

hpnicfLIUserStreamRowStatus.name: hpnicfLIUserStreamRowStatus
hpnicfLIUserStreamRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.
